# Git LFS was declared here for *.mov / *.mp4 but never actually activated
# (git-lfs is not installed; the tracked MP4s are real blobs, not pointers).
# The inert filter lines were removed so new media isn't silently mis-handled.
# If you later want LFS for the large binaries, install git-lfs first, then
# `git lfs track` and re-add the files.

# Line-ending normalization (stop CRLF/LF drift across machines)
* text=auto eol=lf
*.html text eol=lf
*.css  text eol=lf
*.js   text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.bmp binary
*.mp4 binary
*.mov binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
